Rate Command: introducing ratings to application
commitResults.messageBody:
No existing method to rank the contacts in database, other than lexographically.

A rating can be add to all new contact objects and updated whenever needed.
Ratings have to be an integer from 1 to 5 inclusive.

Current rating is displayed plainly as an integer under each PersonCard. Does not stand out to user and can confuse user without any background knowledge of the fields.

A highlighted box with bolded text and a star emoticon will help users easily and intuitively understand what the field stands for, and aids our rating field in achieving what it is supposed to: readability and comprehensibility.

Let's
* Improve the look of the rating field in the GUI

Update Filter Command to add filter by ratings functionality
commitResults.messageBody:
Previous Filter command was only filter by category codes

Current filter command will be able to filter by ratings too.

Enhance this feature by allowing users to filter by rating, i.e.:

`filter ra/3`: filter all contacts with a rating of 3 stars.
`filter c/att ra/5`: filter all accommodation-coded contacts with a rating of 5 stars.
`Rate Command` is redundant as we already have 'Add Command` and `Edit Command` for the addition and modification of `rating` field respectively.
